        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 29 at 1:01PM CDT by NWS Midland/Odessa TX</headline>
        <description>At 100 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Fort Stockton, moving northeast at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Fort Stockton, Firestone Test Track, Imperial, Fort Stockton-Pecos
County Airport, and Imperial Reservoir.

This includes Interstate 10 between mile markers 244 and 270.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
